Misc cleanup / simplifications: - not doing syncDown or syncUp from the main process but instead requesting them through from the sync process - no need to have references to current account, original data (NameFieldFilter keeps track of that) or smartStore (only ContactListLoader talks to SmartStore) - activity only feeds data to NameFieldFilter which feeds it (filtered) to the ContactListAdapter, also NameFieldFilter remembers the filter term => that way when you go back from detail to list, the typed filter still applies - NameFieldFilter's setData (previously called setOrigData) calls filter and so does setFilterTerm
Optional boolean bundle flag to only do a sync down

But only the encrypt() method was updated, not the decrypt method.

We were left with that meaningless and actually dangerous code that can throw ArrayIndexOutOfBoundException.

Testing inserting empty element to full text search indexed soup
Fixing account_type and app_package

Fix for: An empty record saved to smartstore doesn't get a row in the FTS table Impact:
When records is updated, it still doesn't have a row in the FTS table
As a result, record cannot be found with a FTS query.
Also when if more non-empty records are created, their id won't match the record ids in the main soup table and so FTS query returns the wrong records.

How did we find the bug:
SmartSyncExplorerHybrid add creates an empty record before going into the Edit screen.
If you back out from the screen, the record is deleted, if you save it gets updated

Because all FTS fields were empty, no row were created in the FTS table.
When the save happens, there is no row to update.
As a result, those records never show up in the search screen (until the records are synched up and the app is restarted and a sync down bring the data back).

Fix:
Pass the id in the values so that a row actually gets created.

How come we didn't see the bug before?
Existing code works for non-empty record, the id column is auto-filled, and ends up with the same id as the corresponding row in the main soup table.
It's only when no values are passed through that the row is not created.
